headlines.description: — Evan Mobley scored 28 points, fellow All-Star Donovan Mitchell added 23 and the Cleveland Cavaliers broke out to a big early lead and had little trouble against Minnesota, beating the Timberwolves 128-107 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: All-Stars Evan Mobley, Donovan Mitchell pace Cavs to 128-107 win over slow-starting Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 11 of his 19 points in the fourth quarter, and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Orlando Magic 112-106 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young leads Hawks past Magic 112-106

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama had 31 points and 15 rebounds to help the San Antonio Spurs hold off the Washington Wizards 131-121 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Victor Wembanyama's 31 points, 15 rebounds help Spurs to a 131-121 victory over Wizards

headlines.description: — Nic Claxton scored 16 points and the Brooklyn Nets pulled away after LaMelo Ball was lost to another ankle...
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets pull away from Hornets after LaMelo Ball leaves with ankle injury, win 97-89

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 33 points, Kristaps Porzingis added 17 and the Boston Celtics rolled past the Miami Heat 103-85 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum scores 33, Celtics hold Heat to 34% shooting and roll to 103-85 win

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored a season-high 38 points and the Golden State Warriors pulled away in the fourth quarter to beat the Milwaukee Bucks 125-111 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 38 points as Warriors win 125-111 at Milwaukee

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 31 points in three quarters as the Oklahoma City Thunder routed the New Orleans Pelicans 137-101 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 31 and Thunder make franchise-record 27 3s in 137-101 rout of Pelicans

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored a season-high 42 points, including a baseline floater with 2 seconds left in overtime, and the Sacramento Kings beat the depleted Dallas Mavericks 129-128 on Monday...
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan scores 42 points, including OT winner, as Kings edge depleted Mavericks 129-128

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 40 points, Christian Braun had 26 points, and the surging Denver Nuggets beat the Portland Trail Blazers 146-117 on Monday night for their seventh straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 40 and the Nuggets beat the Blazers 146-117 for their 7th straight win

events.name: Utah Jazz at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 14 points, five rebounds and four assists in his Lakers debut as Los Angeles beat the Utah Jazz 132-113 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic a winner in Lakers debut, 132-113 over Jazz
